  "text": "Order Scutigeromorpha Family Scutigeridae Dendrothereua nr. homa Species in the genus Dendrothereua are primarily Neotropical in their distribution, with only a single species (Dendrothereua homa) currently recognized as occurring in the United States [CITATION_1] ). However, this species probably represents a handful of distinct taxa in the southern U. S., which may eventually be sorted out by future taxonomic studies.",
